<br>
Given you current level getting 200 int would be the priority over resists. Resists would come more when you reach the late 40s and by that time you should have plenty of int to fuel your mana pool.<br>
<br>
Again if you have great opportunities on resist gears get them, nothing forces you to wear them until you really need them (I have a full 10 slot bag of resist items at bank that I only wear when I know I'll need).<br>
<br>
Along with the staff I would also recommand getting some jboots. Kitting with the staff is only efficient if you can outrun your foe otherwise better snare to pull so you do not snare self nor get hit on the head trying to.<br>
